HEADWORD: Urva
<hw>Ur"va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The crab-eating ichneumon (<spn>Herpestes
urva</spn>), native of India. The fur is black, annulated with white at
the tip of each hair, and a white streak extends from the mouth to the
shoulder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

